Another quake measuring 8 . 0 - magnitude struck Sichuan in May 2008 leaving nearly 87 , 000 dead or missing . Jiang Haikun , an official with the China Earthquake Networks Centre  s forecasting department , said Saturday  s quake was formed in the same way as the 2008 quake . Both quakes occurred on the Longmen mountain fault zone , he said , which tended to produce powerful tremors along a 500 - kilometre - long belt .